DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       BN_mod_inverse() computes the inverse of aa modulo nn places
       the result in rr ((a*r)%n==1). If rr is NULL, a new BBIIGGNNUUMM
       is created.

       ccttxx is a previously allocated BBNN_CCTTXX used for temporary
       variables. rr may be the same BBIIGGNNUUMM as aa or nn.

